Schedule Smarter with Priority Scheduling

Priority scheduling for CRM Analytics recipes automatically manages your run queue. It prioritizes smaller and faster runs while ensuring that larger and longer runs are completed on time. Priority is automatically calculated based on factors such as historic runtime, dataset input size, and CSV file size.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

For example, you schedule three recipes to run at the same time. One is larger with more rows and runs for 30 minutes. The other two are smaller with fewer rows and run for three minutes. The larger recipeâ€™s run request arrives a millisecond before the shorter requests.

From Setup, enter Analytics in the Quick Find box, then select Settings.
Select Use priority scheduling for recipe and dataflow requests.
Click Save.
You can disable priority scheduling at any time to return to a first in, first out queue.
